gomodel:SYNGO_1125  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The equilibrative nucleoside transporter (ENT)1 is expressed at synapses. Pre-embedding immunoperoxidase and -immunogold labelling demonstrates the presence of ENT1 immunoreactivity in some postsynaptic terminals (Fig 3F, G).\n\nThe specificity of the antibody used (anti-rENT1227-290) was tested by ELISA, Western Blotting and IHC (Fig. 1).. Experimental description: Wistar rats (bred in-house) were given a lethal dose of Sagatal" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
